    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen Nvim receives a CSI sequence with 17 or more arguments, it outputs the following error message and crashes:\r\n```\r\n*** stack smashing detected ***: terminated\r\n                                           Aborted (core dumped)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe cause of this issue is in the `peekkey_csi` function at line 533 of `driver-csi.c` in libtermkey. The buffer that stores the arguments for the CSI sequence is declared with a size of 16, causing a buffer overflow when trying to store the 17th argument.\r\nApplying the following patch to `driver-csi.c` can mitigate the problem:\r\n```patch\r\n532,533c532,533\r\n<   size_t args = 16;\r\n<   long arg[16];\r\n---\r\n>   size_t args = 32;\r\n>   long arg[32];\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to the documentation, Nvim sends `CSI ? u CSI c` during startup. Some terminal emulators respond to this with `CSI ? 65;1;2;3;4;6;7;8;9;15;18;21;22;29;39;42;44 c`, which has more than 16 arguments. As a result, Nvim crashes during startup.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n1. Send `\\x1b[?65;1;2;3;4;6;7;8;9;15;18;21;22;29;39;42;44c` to Nvim\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo crash\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.1, libtermkey 0.22\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0.1628\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n`Linux alarmpi 6.1.35-4-rpi-ARCH #1 SMP Sun Jun 25 13:05:28 MDT 2023 armv7l GNU/Linux`\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nRLogin (x64) Version 2.28.3 (2023/07/03) https://github.com/kmiya-culti/RLogin\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n`sudo pacman -Syu neovim`",
